<div id="bottomLeftRight">

<h2>Upcoming Events</h2>

<h3><a href="http://live.gnome.org/Hackfests/GNOME.Asia2011">GNOME 3.0 Bangalore Hackfest</a></h3>
<i>March 28 - April 1 2011, Bangalore, India</i>

<p>We are hosting a <strong>5 days hackfest</strong> for the release, documentation and marketing teams focusing on the <a
href="http://www.gnome3.org">GNOME 3.0</a> release. This will ensure some heavy testing of the code during the last week before the official release, as well as preparing the release to happen in an optimal way.</p>

<p>Please let us know you are coming by <a href="http://live.gnome.org/Hackfests/GNOME.Asia2011">registering on the hackfest page</a>.</p>

<h3><a href="http://www.gnome.asia">GNOME Asia Summit 2011</a></h3>
<i>April 2-3 2011, Bangalore, India</i>
<p>Right after the <a href="http://live.gnome.org/Hackfests/GNOME.Asia2011">GNOME 3.0 Bangalore Hackfest</a>, we will jump on the opportunity of having a lot of the GNOME developers already on site to <strong>aim for the greatest <a href="http://www.gnome.asia">GNOME.Asia Summit</a> of all time</strong>. Now in its forth year, <a href="http://www.gnome.asia">GNOME.Asia Summit</a> will have the pleasure to continue to bring GNOME to users and developers in Asia and more specifically India this year, but also to celebrate the release of <a href="http://www.gnome3.org">GNOME 3.0</a> with the people who actually write the software!</p>

<p>Stay tuned and visit <a href="http://www.gnome.asia">Gnome.Asia</a> regularly for the latest information!</p>

<h3><a href="http://www.desktopsummit.org/">Desktop Summit 2011</a></h3>
<i>August 6-12, 2011, Berlin, Germany</i>
<p>The Desktop Summit is the get-together of the yearly free software conferences Akademy and GUADEC. This year, the Desktop Summit will take place at the Humboldt University in Berlin. The event will feature keynotes, talks, workshops and social activities. We expect well over a thousand participants. Registration is coming up soon.</p>

